Could we please have a separate test target in the build.xml file so 
that &quot;ant test&quot; works as one would expect? Something like this should do 
the trick:

	&lt;target name=&quot;test&quot; depends=&quot;build&quot;&gt;
		&lt;java classname=&quot;org.junit.runner.JUnitCore&quot; fork=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
		    &lt;!--There must be a more intelligent way to do this--&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.AnnotationTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.AssertionTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.CommandLineTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.ForwardCompatibilityTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.OldTests&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.PreJUnit4TestCaseRunnerTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.TestMethodTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;arg value=&quot;org.junit.tests.TextListenerTest&quot;/&gt;
			&lt;classpath&gt;
				&lt;pathelement location=&quot;${dist}&quot; /&gt;
				&lt;pathelement location=&quot;${dist}/junit.jar&quot; /&gt;
			&lt;/classpath&gt;
		&lt;/java&gt;

	&lt;/target&gt;

Then the dist target could depend on the test rather than the build:

	&lt;target name=&quot;dist&quot; depends=&quot;test&quot;&gt;
		&lt;delete dir=&quot;${dist}&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;mkdir dir=&quot;${dist}&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;jar
			jarfile=&quot;${dist}/src.jar&quot;
			basedir=&quot;.&quot;
			excludes=&quot;**/*.jar, junit/tests/**, junit/samples/**, **/*.class, 
doc/**, README.html, .classpath, .project, cpl-v10.html&quot;
		/&gt;
		&lt;jar
			jarfile=&quot;${dist}/junit.jar&quot;
			basedir=&quot;.&quot;
			excludes=&quot;**/*.jar, junit/tests/**, junit/samples/**, **/*.java, 
doc/**, README.html,  build.xml, jar-manifest.txt, .classpath, .project, 
cpl-v10.html&quot;
		/&gt;
		&lt;copy todir=&quot;${dist}/junit/samples&quot;&gt;
			&lt;fileset dir=&quot;junit/samples&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;/copy&gt;
		&lt;copy todir=&quot;${dist}/junit/tests&quot;&gt;
			&lt;fileset dir=&quot;junit/tests&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;/copy&gt;

		&lt;mkdir dir=&quot;${dist}/javadoc&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;javadoc
			sourcepath=&quot;.&quot;
			packagenames=&quot;org.junit, org.junit.runner&quot;
			destdir=&quot;${dist}/javadoc&quot;
			author=&quot;false&quot;
			version=&quot;false&quot;
			use=&quot;false&quot;
			windowtitle=&quot;JUnit API&quot;
			stylesheetfile=&quot;stylesheet.css&quot;
		/&gt;
		&lt;copy todir=&quot;${dist}/doc&quot;&gt;
			&lt;fileset dir=&quot;doc&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;/copy&gt;		
		&lt;copy file=&quot;README.html&quot; tofile=&quot;${dist}/README.html&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;copy file=&quot;cpl-v10.html&quot; tofile=&quot;${dist}/cpl-v10.html&quot; /&gt;

	&lt;/target&gt;

